text:
According to the statement released by the Pakistani Foreign Ministry spokesperson on the boat capsizing incident in southern Greece , four Pakistanis who lost their lives in the accident have been identified.
“We are deeply saddened to announce that, according to the latest information provided by the Greek authorities, four Pakistanis were among those killed in Saturday’s boat capsizing south of the Greek island of Crete ,” the statement said.
“Our mission in Athens is in contact with the Greek authorities to facilitate the survivors and repatriate the bodies.”
Earlier, the Foreign Ministry had said that Pakistan’s embassy in Athens is in contact with the Hellenic Coast Guard and Chania Coast Guard which are directly dealing with search and rescue operations. Embassy officials have reached Crete to meet the rescued Pakistanis and provide them with all possible assistance.
A migrant ship capsized near the southern Greek island between Friday and Saturday night, leaving five dead and several missing, while 39 people were rescued by the Greek navy.
