A statement released by the Prime Minister’s House on Sunday said “human trafficking is a heinous crime, claiming many lives and destroying many homes every year.”
The Prime Minister directed Home Minister Mohsin Naqvi to submit an inquiry report into the incident as soon as possible and said “such people should be identified and punished severely so that they do not repeat such heinous acts.”
The Prime Minister further said, “Concrete measures should be taken to prevent such incidents in the future.”
Home Minister Mohsin Naqvi has formed a committee headed by Additional Secretary Home which will investigate the boat accident and submit a report to the Home Minister within five days.
Home Minister Mohsin Naqvi said that “human trafficking is a crime in which the mafia involved has destroyed many houses.”
He also instructed the Federal Investigation Agency (FIA) to launch nationwide operations against mafia involved in human trafficking.
